'''March 21''' is the 21st day of the month {{ill|March (Lunisolar)|ja|3月 (旧暦)|lt=March (Yayoi)|qq=|12=draft|12=draft}}, the 3rd month of the traditional {{ill|Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|ja|旧暦|1=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|1=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|11=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|qq=|12=draft|12=draft}}. Its {{ill|Rokuyō|ja|六曜|qq=|12=draft|12=draft}} day is {{ill|Taian|ja|大安|qq=|12=draft|12=draft}}.

== Events ==
* {{ill|Daibō|ja|大宝|qq=|12=draft|12=draft}} 1st year ({{ill|Julian calendar|1=Julian calendar|2=ja|3=ユリウス暦|4=zh|5=儒略曆|6=ru|7=Юлианский_календарь|8=de|9=Julianischer_Kalender|10=es|11=Calendario juliano|ja|ユリウス暦|1=Julian calendar|2=ja|3=ユリウス暦|4=zh|5=儒略曆|6=ru|7=Юлианский_календарь|8=de|9=Julianischer_Kalender|10=es|11=Calendario juliano|qq=|12=draft|12=draft}} [[701]] {{ill|May 3|ja|5月3日|qq=|12=draft|12=draft}}) – Following a gold offering from Tsushima, the era name was changed to {{ill|Daibō|ja|大宝|qq=|12=draft|12=draft}}.
* {{ill|Kannin|ja|寛仁|qq=|12=draft|12=draft}} 3rd year ({{ill|Julian calendar|1=Julian calendar|2=ja|3=ユリウス暦|4=zh|5=儒略曆|6=ru|7=Юлианский_календарь|8=de|9=Julianischer_Kalender|10=es|11=Calendario juliano|ja|ユリウス暦|1=Julian calendar|2=ja|3=ユリウス暦|4=zh|5=儒略曆|6=ru|7=Юлианский_календарь|8=de|9=Julianischer_Kalender|10=es|11=Calendario juliano|qq=|12=draft|12=draft}} [[1019]] {{ill|April 28|ja|4月28日|qq=|12=draft|12=draft}}) – {{ill|Fujiwara no Michinaga|ja|藤原道長|qq=|12=draft|12=draft}} retired from court life and began the construction of {{ill|Muryōju-in|ja|無量寿院|qq=|12=draft|12=draft}}.
* {{ill|Genkyū|ja|元久|qq=|12=draft|12=draft}} 1st year ({{ill|Julian calendar|1=Julian calendar|2=ja|3=ユリウス暦|4=zh|5=儒略曆|6=ru|7=Юлианский_календарь|8=de|9=Julianischer_Kalender|10=es|11=Calendario juliano|ja|ユリウス暦|1=Julian calendar|2=ja|3=ユリウス暦|4=zh|5=儒略曆|6=ru|7=Юлианский_календарь|8=de|9=Julianischer_Kalender|10=es|11=Calendario juliano|qq=|12=draft|12=draft}} [[1204]] {{ill|April 26|ja|4月26日|qq=|12=draft|12=draft}}) – During the rebellion of the Taira clan on the 3rd day, known as the {{ill|Mikka Taira no Ran|ja|三日Taira Clanの乱|qq=|12=draft|12=draft}}, the forces of 【平賀朝雅】 subdued the remnants of the Taira clan in Iga and Ise.
* {{ill|Keichō|ja|慶長|qq=|12=draft|12=draft}} 17th year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar|2=ja|3=グレゴリオ暦|4=fr|5=Calendrier grégorien|6=de|7=Gregorianischer Kalender|8=tl|9=Kalendaryong Gregoryano|10=ru|11=Григорианский календарь|ja|グレゴリオ暦|qq=|12=draft|12=draft}} [[1612]] {{ill|April 21|ja|4月21日|qq=|12=draft|12=draft}}) – The Tokugawa shogunate issued a decree banning Christianity directly under its control; the measure was expanded nationwide the following year.
== Births ==


== Deaths ==
* {{ill|Shōwa|ja|承和|qq=|12=draft|12=draft}} 2nd year ({{ill|Julian calendar|1=Julian calendar|2=ja|3=ユリウス暦|4=zh|5=儒略曆|6=ru|7=Юлианский_календарь|8=de|9=Julianischer_Kalender|10=es|11=Calendario juliano|ja|ユリウス暦|1=Julian calendar|2=ja|3=ユリウス暦|4=zh|5=儒略曆|6=ru|7=Юлианский_календарь|8=de|9=Julianischer_Kalender|10=es|11=Calendario juliano|qq=|12=draft|12=draft}} [[835]] {{ill|April 22|ja|4月22日|qq=|12=draft|12=draft}}) – In this year, the monk {{ill|Kūkai|ja|空海|qq=|12=draft|12=draft}} (also known as Kōbō-Daishi), founder of the Shingon sect, is recorded as having died (note: some sources may differ on dates).
* {{ill|Kashō|ja|嘉祥|qq=|12=draft|12=draft}} 3rd year ({{ill|Julian calendar|1=Julian calendar|2=ja|3=ユリウス暦|4=zh|5=儒略曆|6=ru|7=Юлианский_календарь|8=de|9=Julianischer_Kalender|10=es|11=Calendario juliano|ja|ユリウス暦|1=Julian calendar|2=ja|3=ユリウス暦|4=zh|5=儒略曆|6=ru|7=Юлианский_календарь|8=de|9=Julianischer_Kalender|10=es|11=Calendario juliano|qq=|12=draft|12=draft}} [[850]] {{ill|May 6|ja|5月6日|qq=|12=draft|12=draft}}) – {{ill|Emperor Nimmei|ja|仁明天皇|qq=|12=draft|12=draft}}, the 54th Emperor of Japan, died (born [[810]]).
* {{ill|Keian|ja|慶安|qq=|12=draft|12=draft}} 3rd year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar|2=ja|3=グレゴリオ暦|4=fr|5=Calendrier grégorien|6=de|7=Gregorianischer Kalender|8=tl|9=Kalendaryong Gregoryano|10=ru|11=Григорианский календарь|ja|グレゴリオ暦|qq=|12=draft|12=draft}} [[1650]] {{ill|April 21|ja|4月21日|qq=|12=draft|12=draft}}) – The famous swordsman and Kenjutsu master {{ill|Yagyū Sanjūrō|ja|柳生三厳|qq=|12=draft|12=draft}} (also known as Yagyū Jūbei) died (born [[1607]]).
* {{ill|Bunsei|ja|文政|qq=|12=draft|12=draft}} 5th year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar|2=ja|3=グレゴリオ暦|4=fr|5=Calendrier grégorien|6=de|7=Gregorianischer Kalender|8=tl|9=Kalendaryong Gregoryano|10=ru|11=Григорианский календарь|ja|グレゴリオ暦|qq=|12=draft|12=draft}} [[1822]] {{ill|May 12|ja|5月12日|qq=|12=draft|12=draft}}) – {{ill|Matsudaira Saitō|ja|松平斉恒|qq=|12=draft|12=draft}}, the 8th lord of the Matsue Domain, died (born [[1791]]).
* {{ill|Genji|ja|元治|qq=|12=draft|12=draft}} 1st year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar|2=ja|3=グレゴリオ暦|4=fr|5=Calendrier grégorien|6=de|7=Gregorianischer Kalender|8=tl|9=Kalendaryong Gregoryano|10=ru|11=Григорианский календарь|ja|グレゴリオ暦|qq=|12=draft|12=draft}} [[1864]] {{ill|April 26|ja|4月26日|qq=|12=draft|12=draft}}) – {{ill|Horita Masamutsumi|ja|堀田正睦|qq=|12=draft|12=draft}}, a senior councilor (Rōjū) of the Tokugawa shogunate, died (born [[1810]]).

