{{Not to be confused with|March 21|qq=March 21}}[[Category:Days of the Japanese Lunisolar Calendar]]<!--why is this category always showing up as 347 members?--> {{afc comment|1=This article as with the other date articles is relatively limited in scope to Japan. Reviewing the translation of this is good and also adding content translated from Chinese and Korean wikipedias will also be good. Both wikipedias are also relatively centered around their own countries for their Lunisolar calendar dates[[User:Immanuelle|Immanuelle]] ([[User talk:Immanuelle|talk]]) 00:16, 28 April 2025 (UTC)}} {{Globalize|article|Japan|date=April 2025}} {{Expand Chinese|1=三月廿一|topic=hist|date=April 2025}} {{Expand Korean|1=음력 3월 21일|topic=hist|date=April 2025}} {{Lunisolar March|qq=}} '''March 21''' is the 21st day of the month {{ill|March (Lunisolar)|ja|3月 (旧暦)|lt=March (Yayoi)|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/March (Lunisolar)|qq=}}, the 3rd month of the traditional {{ill|Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|ja|旧暦|1=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|1=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|11=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|13=User:Immanuelle/Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|qq=}}. Its {{ill|Rokuyō|ja|六曜|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Rokuyō|qq=}} day is {{ill|Taian|ja|大安|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Taian|qq=}}.
== Events == * [[:en:Taiho|Daibō]] 1st year ([[:en:Julian calendar|Julian calendar]] [[:en:701|701]] [[:en:May 3|May 3]]) – Following a gold offering from Tsushima, the era name was changed to [[:en:Taiho|Daibō]]. * [[:en:Kannin|Kannin]] 3rd year ([[:en:Julian calendar|Julian calendar]] [[:en:1019|1019]] [[:en:April 28|April 28]]) – [[:en:Fujiwara no Michinaga|Fujiwara no Michinaga]] retired from court life and began the construction of {{ill|Muryōju-in|ja|無量寿院|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Muryōju-in|qq=}}. * [[:en:Genkyū|Genkyū]] 1st year ([[:en:Julian calendar|Julian calendar]] [[:en:1204|1204]] [[:en:April 26|April 26]]) – During the rebellion of the Taira clan on the 3rd day, known as the {{ill|Mikka Taira no Ran|ja|三日Taira Clanの乱|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Mikka Taira no Ran|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}}, the forces of 【平賀朝雅】 subdued the remnants of the Taira clan in Iga and Ise. * [[:en:Keichō|Keichō]] 17th year ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] [[:en:1612|1612]] [[:en:April 21|April 21]]) – The Tokugawa shogunate issued a decree banning Christianity directly under its control; the measure was expanded nationwide the following year. == Births ==
== Deaths == * [[:en:Jōwa|Shōwa]] 2nd year ([[:en:Julian calendar|Julian calendar]] [[:en:835|835]] [[:en:April 22|April 22]]) – In this year, the monk [[:en:Kūkai|Kūkai]] (also known as Kōbō-Daishi), founder of the Shingon sect, is recorded as having died (note: some sources may differ on dates). * [[:en:Kashō|Kashō]] 3rd year ([[:en:Julian calendar|Julian calendar]] [[:en:850|850]] [[:en:May 6|May 6]]) – [[:en:Emperor Ninmyō|Emperor Nimmei]], the 54th Emperor of Japan, died (born [[:en:810|810]]). * [[:en:Keian|Keian]] 3rd year ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] [[:en:1650|1650]] [[:en:April 21|April 21]]) – The famous swordsman and Kenjutsu master [[:en:Yagyū Jūbei Mitsuyoshi|Yagyū Sanjūrō]] (also known as Yagyū Jūbei) died (born [[:en:1607|1607]]). * [[:en:Bunsei|Bunsei]] 5th year ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] [[:en:1822|1822]] [[:en:May 12|May 12]]) – {{ill|Matsudaira Saitō|ja|松平斉恒|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Matsudaira Saitō|qq=}}, the 8th lord of the Matsue Domain, died (born [[:en:1791|1791]]). * [[:en:Genji era|Genji]] 1st year ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] [[:en:1864|1864]] [[:en:April 26|April 26]]) – [[:en:Hotta Masayoshi|Horita Masamutsumi]], a senior councilor (Rōjū) of the Tokugawa shogunate, died (born [[:en:1810|1810]]).
